{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GRDAv99fbfQVprXkv6N1EP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 11-3: State Reconciliation on Session Start\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want state consistency verified at the start of every session,\n     9→So that desyncs from crashes or manual edits are caught immediately.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `sprint-state.json` and `sprint-status.yaml` are out of sync, when harness-run Step 1 pre-flight runs `reconcileState()`, then `sprint-state.json` is authoritative and `sprint-status.yaml` is regenerated <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→\n    15→## Technical Notes\n    16→\n    17→**Decision 1 (Unified State)** and **Decision 11 (Process Enforcement)** -- state reconciliation is one of five embedded gates in harness-run Step 1 pre-flight.\n    18→\n    19→Create `reconcileState()` function that runs at the very start of `harness-run`:\n    20→\n    21→1. Read `sprint-state.json` (the authority)\n    22→2. If it has no `version` field, trigger migration from story 11-1\n    23→3. Regenerate `sprint-status.yaml` from `sprint-state.json` (overwrites any manual edits to YAML)\n    24→4. Check for orphaned state files (`.story_retries`, `.flagged_stories`) and merge them if found\n    25→5. Validate internal consistency: every story in `stories` should belong to an epic in `epics`\n    26→6. Log any corrections made: `[INFO] Reconciled: regenerated sprint-status.yaml`, `[INFO] Reconciled: merged .story_retries into sprint-state.json`\n    27→\n    28→This runs as part of Step 1 pre-flight in `src/commands/run.ts`, alongside Docker pre-check (story 14-3) and orphan cleanup.\n    29→\n    30→The function should be idempotent -- running it on an already-consistent state is a no-op.\n    31→\n    32→## Files to Change\n    33→\n    34→- `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` — Add `reconcileState()` function that validates and regenerates derived views\n    35→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Call `reconcileState()` in Step 1 pre-flight, before story selection\n    36→- `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/reconciliation.test.ts` — Test: out-of-sync YAML gets regenerated, orphaned files get merged, consistent state is no-op\n    37→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011K77Q1Nc8EiPZnCgrdVKHN","session_id":"01503c00-15e6-46f1-b837-b4628ff69656","uuid":"a48d01bf-a25c-4f86-9fa5-94a53f63d6f5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:32:43.150Z"}
