{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011oAgoYVxsCMFQGsh4V9FL9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 11-2: sprint-status.yaml Becomes Derived View\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: done\n     5→\n     6→## Story\n     7→\n     8→As a developer,\n     9→I want `sprint-status.yaml` generated from `sprint-state.json`,\n    10→So that there's one source of truth with a human-readable view.\n    11→\n    12→## Acceptance Criteria\n    13→\n    14→- [x] AC1: Given `sprint-state.json` has story statuses, when `generateSprintStatusYaml()` is called, then it writes a valid YAML file matching the current sprint-status.yaml format <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [x] AC2: Given a story status changes in `sprint-state.json`, when `writeSprintState()` completes, then `sprint-status.yaml` is regenerated automatically <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC3: Given harness-run reads story statuses, when it queries state, then it reads from `sprint-state.json` directly (not sprint-status.yaml) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→\n    18→## Technical Notes\n    19→\n    20→**Decision 1 (Unified State).** `sprint-status.yaml` transitions from source of truth to derived view. All readers must switch to `sprint-state.json`.\n    21→\n    22→Create `generateSprintStatusYaml()` function that:\n    23→1. Reads `sprint-state.json`\n    24→2. Transforms `stories` and `epics` into the current YAML format (epic groupings, story status lines)\n    25→3. Writes `sprint-status.yaml` using the same YAML structure that exists today\n    26→\n    27→Hook this into `writeSprintState()` so every state write auto-regenerates the YAML view. This ensures the human-readable file is always current without being a source of truth.\n    28→\n    29→Current readers of `sprint-status.yaml` that must switch to `sprint-state.json`:\n    30→- `src/lib/beads-sync.ts` — `readSprintStatus()` parses YAML to get story statuses\n    31→- `src/commands/status.ts` — reads sprint-status.yaml for display\n    32→- `src/commands/run.ts` — reads story statuses for selection\n    33→- `src/modules/sprint/selector.ts` — story selection reads statuses\n    34→- `src/modules/sprint/reporter.ts` — progress reporting\n    35→\n    36→The `readSprintStatus()` function in `src/lib/beads-sync.ts` should be replaced with direct reads from `sprint-state.json` via `readSprintState()`.\n    37→\n    38→The YAML generation can live in `src/lib/sync/sprint-yaml.ts` (anticipating Epic 12 restructuring) or temporarily in `src/modules/sprint/state.ts`.\n    39→\n    40→## Tasks/Subtasks\n    41→\n    42→- [x] 1. Add `generateSprintStatusYaml()` to `src/modules/sprint/state.ts`\n    43→  - [x] 1.1 Create `getStoryStatusesFromState()` — derive flat status map from SprintState\n    44→  - [x] 1.2 Create `generateSprintStatusYaml()` — produce YAML with epic groupings, sorted by epic/story number\n    45→  - [x] 1.3 Create `sprintStatusYamlPath()` — return path to sprint-status.yaml\n    46→  - [x] 1.4 Create `writeSprintStatusYaml()` — best-effort write of derived YAML view\n    47→- [x] 2. Hook YAML generation into `writeStateAtomic()` so every state write regenerates the YAML\n    48→- [x] 3. Switch consumers from `readSprintStatus()` (YAML) to `readSprintStatusFromState()` (JSON)\n    49→  - [x] 3.1 Add `readSprintStatusFromState()` to sprint module index\n    50→  - [x] 3.2 Switch `src/commands/run.ts` from `readSprintStatus` to `readSprintStatusFromState`\n    51→  - [x] 3.3 Switch `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` from `readSprintStatus` to `readSprintStatusFromState`\n    52→  - [x] 3.4 Verify `src/commands/status.ts` already reads from sprint-state.json (confirmed — no changes needed)\n    53→  - [x] 3.5 Verify `src/modules/sprint/selector.ts` already works from SprintState objects (confirmed — no changes needed)\n    54→  - [x] 3.6 Verify `src/modules/sprint/reporter.ts` already works from SprintState objects (confirmed — no changes needed)\n    55→- [x] 4. Update test mocks in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` to mock `readSprintStatusFromState` from new module\n    56→- [x] 5. Write tests for new functions in `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/sprint-yaml.test.ts`\n    57→  - [x] 5.1 Tests for `getStoryStatusesFromState`\n    58→  - [x] 5.2 Tests for `generateSprintStatusYaml` (valid YAML, epic grouping, sorting, status mapping)\n    59→  - [x] 5.3 Tests for `writeStateAtomic` regenerating YAML on every write\n    60→  - [x] 5.4 Tests for `sprintStatusYamlPath`\n    61→\n    62→## Dev Agent Record\n    63→\n    64→### Implementation Plan\n    65→\n    66→- Place YAML generation in `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` (co-located with `writeStateAtomic`)\n    67→- Hook generation as a best-effort side effect after atomic JSON write\n    68→- Create `readSprintStatusFromState()` in sprint module index as a drop-in replacement for the old `readSprintStatus()` that parsed YAML\n    69→- Switch `run.ts` and `onboard-checks.ts` to use the new JSON-backed function\n    70→- `status.ts`, `selector.ts`, and `reporter.ts` already read from SprintState objects — no changes needed\n    71→- `beads-sync.ts` keeps its `readSprintStatus()` for backward compatibility (still used by its own sync functions and tests)\n    72→\n    73→### Completion Notes\n    74→\n    75→All 3 acceptance criteria satisfied:\n    76→- AC1: `generateSprintStatusYaml()` produces valid YAML matching the sprint-status.yaml format with epic groupings, story ordering, and correct status values. 14 dedicated tests verify this.\n    77→- AC2: `writeStateAtomic()` calls `writeSprintStatusYaml()` after every successful JSON write, ensuring the YAML view is always current.\n    78→- AC3: `run.ts` and `onboard-checks.ts` now read from `sprint-state.json` via `readSprintStatusFromState()`. `status.ts`, `selector.ts`, and `reporter.ts` already used SprintState objects.\n    79→\n    80→Full test suite: 3424 tests pass across 124 test files, zero regressions.\n    81→\n    82→## File List\n    83→\n    84→- `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` — Added `generateSprintStatusYaml()`, `getStoryStatusesFromState()`, `sprintStatusYamlPath()`, `writeSprintStatusYaml()`, `yamlStatus()`, `parseStoryKey()`; modified `writeStateAtomic()` to regenerate YAML\n    85→- `src/modules/sprint/index.ts` — Added exports for `generateSprintStatusYaml`, `getStoryStatusesFromState`, `readSprintStatusFromState`\n    86→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Switched from `readSprintStatus` (beads-sync YAML) to `readSprintStatusFromState` (sprint module JSON)\n    87→- `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` — Switched from `readSprintStatus` (beads-sync YAML) to `readSprintStatusFromState` (sprint module JSON)\n    88→- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — Updated mock to include `readSprintStatusFromState` in sprint module mock\n    89→- `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/sprint-yaml.test.ts` — New: 14 tests for YAML generation and status derivation\n    90→\n    91→## Change Log\n    92→\n    93→- 2026-03-24: Implemented story 11-2. sprint-status.yaml is now a derived view auto-generated from sprint-state.json on every state write. All primary consumers switched to reading from sprint-state.json.\n    94→\n    95→## Files to Change (Original)\n    96→\n    97→- `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` — Add `generateSprintStatusYaml()`, call it at end of `writeSprintState()`\n    98→- `src/lib/beads-sync.ts` — Replace `readSprintStatus()` YAML parsing with `readSprintState()` JSON reads\n    99→- `src/commands/status.ts` — Switch from sprint-status.yaml to sprint-state.json reads\n   100→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Switch status reads to sprint-state.json\n   101→- `src/modules/sprint/selector.ts` — Ensure story selection reads from sprint-state.json\n   102→- `src/modules/sprint/reporter.ts` — Switch progress reads to sprint-state.json\n   103→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011K77Q1Nc8EiPZnCgrdVKHN","session_id":"01503c00-15e6-46f1-b837-b4628ff69656","uuid":"17499439-2eca-4e45-84eb-614610a3d1cf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:32:44.877Z"}
