{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J8obBNAKVKfqgNEf6KsEED","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Implementation Summary\n\n**Story 11-3: State Reconciliation on Session Start** — all 6 tasks completed, all 12 ACs addressed, story marked `review`.\n\n### Files Changed\n\n1. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/state.ts`\n   - Added `ReconciliationResult` interface (Task 2)\n   - Added `reconcileState()` function (Task 1) implementing the algorithm from the technical notes: reads state (triggering v1-to-v2 migration if needed), merges orphaned `.story_retries` (max strategy), merges orphaned `.flagged_stories` (set union + dedup), validates epic consistency (auto-creates missing epic entries), regenerates YAML unconditionally, writes state atomically only if mutations occurred\n\n2. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/index.ts`\n   - Imported and re-exported `reconcileState` and `ReconciliationResult` (Task 4)\n\n3. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts`\n   - Added `reconcileState` import and call in Step 1 pre-flight between plugin dir check and sprint status read (Task 3). Best-effort: logs corrections on success, logs warning on failure, never aborts the run.\n\n4. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/__tests__/reconciliation.test.ts` (new)\n   - 14 test cases covering: YAML regeneration on desync, orphaned `.story_retries` merge+delete, max(file, state) strategy, orphaned `.flagged_stories` merge+dedup+delete, missing epic auto-creation, existing epics preserved, consistent state no-op (no writes), v1 state migration trigger, malformed orphan file handling, logging correctness, combined multi-correction scenario (Task 5)\n\n5. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`\n   - Added `reconcileStateMock` to hoisted mocks and sprint module mock to prevent test regressions from the new import\n\n6. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start.md`\n   - Status changed to `review`, all ACs and Tasks checked\n\n### Verification\n\n- `npx tsc --noEmit`: zero new type errors (all errors are pre-existing in unrelated test files)\n- `npx vitest run`: 125 test files, 3447 tests, all passing, 0 regressions\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Pre-existing type errors**: `npx tsc --noEmit` has ~60 pre-existing type errors across `bridge.test.ts`, `run.test.ts`, `stack.test.ts`, `status.test.ts`, `verify-env.test.ts`, and `lib/state.ts`. None introduced by this story.\n- **Readonly mutation workaround**: The `SprintState` type uses `readonly` properties throughout. `reconcileState()` works with a deep-cloned copy via `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...))` and uses type assertions (`as { retries: ... }`) to mutate the clone. This is the same pattern used elsewhere in the codebase but adds a small runtime cost for the deep clone.\n- **YAML always regenerated**: Per the story spec, YAML regeneration always happens even in the no-op case. This means `reconcileState()` always performs one file write (the YAML) even when state is consistent. The story's technical notes say this is \"cheap and ensures freshness\" but it could be optimized to skip if content hasn't changed."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5ecaf79af154e00d (use SendMessage with to: 'a5ecaf79af154e00d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 66034\ntool_uses: 41\nduration_ms: 610030</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01503c00-15e6-46f1-b837-b4628ff69656","uuid":"5a38048d-4d65-478b-8b1f-2912b5998d47","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:45:34.034Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for r