/sprint/__tests__/reconciliation.test.ts` (new)\n   - 14 test cases covering: YAML regeneration on desync, orphaned `.story_retries` merge+delete, max(file, state) strategy, orphaned `.flagged_stories` merge+dedup+delete, missing epic auto-creation, existing epics preserved, consistent state no-op (no writes), v1 state migration trigger, malformed orphan file handling, logging correctness, combined multi-correction scenario (Task 5)\n\n5. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`\n   - Added `reconcileStateMock` to hoisted mocks and sprint module mock to prevent test regressions from the new import\n\n6. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start.md`\n   - Status changed to `review`, all ACs and Tasks checked\n\n### Verification\n\n- `npx tsc --noEmit`: zero new type errors (all errors are pre-existing in unrelated test files)\n- `npx vitest run`: 125 test files, 3447 tests, all passing, 0 regressions\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Pre-existing type errors**: `npx tsc --noEmit` has ~60 pre-existing type errors across `bridge.test.ts`, `run.test.ts`, `stack.test.ts`, `status.test.ts`, `verify-env.test.ts`, and `lib/state.ts`. None introduced by this story.\n- **Readonly mutation workaround**: The `SprintState` type uses `readonly` properties throughout. `reconcileState()` works with a deep-cloned copy via `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...))` and uses type assertions (`as { retries: ... }`) to mutate the clone. This is the same pattern used elsewhere in the codebase but adds a small runtime cost for the deep clone.\n- **YAML always regenerated**: Per the story spec, YAML regeneration always happens even in the no-op case. This means `reconcileState()` always performs one file write (the YAML) even when state is consistent. The story's technical notes say this is \"cheap and ensures freshness\" but it could be optimized to skip if content hasn't changed."}],"tota